## Table of Data Types
| Data Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| VARCHAR or NVARCHAR | Variable-length character string. Max size is specified in parenthesis. Can store up to 255 characters. |
| CHAR or NCHAR | Fixed-length character string. Max size is specified in parenthesis. Can store up to 255 characters. |
| INT | Can be use to store normal numbers |
| DECIMAL or NUMERIC | They are used to store decimal numbers accurately. "p" represents the precision, that is, the number of significant digits that are stored for values, and "s" represents the scale, that is, the number of digits that can be stored following the decimal point. |
| FLOAT or DOUBLE | They are used to store floating point numbers, which can represent values with decimals and a wider range than DECIMAL. |
| DATE | Can be use to store date and time |
| TIME | Can be use to store time |
| DATETIME or TIMESTAMP | Can be use to store both date and time preceded by a time zone offset or time zone region name. |
| BOOLEAN | This data type is used to store Boolean values, which are values that are either true or false. |
| BLOB or CLOB | They are used to store large amounts of binary or character data, respectively. |
| JSON | This data type is used to store JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) data. |
| ENUM | This data type is used to store a list of options. |